CASTRO MEETS CARDINAL

SANTIAGO, Chile--Cuban Premier Fidel Castro is greeted by

Cardinal Raul Silva Henriquez of Santiago during the Cuban leader's

recent visit to Chile. During his 11-day stay, Premier Castro

toured the nation, visiting mines, factories, urban areas and

farming regions. He reportedly told the Chilean prelate that

Christianity and Marxism "should work together to liberate

all people."
